Token.Abstract: Tealium is the main class for the Tealium Library.
Starts an instance of the Tealium Mobile Library for a given key with the given configuration object.

Parameter.Name: key
Parameter.Abstract: NSString identifier for the library instance

Parameter.Name: configuration
Parameter.Abstract: TEALConfiguration instance with valid Account/Profile/Enviroment properties.

Token.Abstract: Returns an instance of the library for the given key, or NIL if such an instance has not been previously initialized.

Parameter.Name: key
Parameter.Abstract: NSString identifier for the library instance.

Token.Abstract: Removes and nils out an instance of the library with the given key.

Parameter.Name: key
Parameter.Abstract: NSString identifier for the library instance to remove.

Token.Abstract: Optional delegate primarily for monitoring or manipulating dispatch data.

ReturnValue.Abstract: The current delegate of the library instance

Token.Abstract: Set the library delegate for overriding and or monitoring dispatch processes.

Parameter.Name: delegate
Parameter.Abstract: Any object that implements one or more optional Tealium Delegate protocols.

Token.Abstract: Sends an event to Collect. Event are packaged with any custom key/value data sources passed in along with the default datasources provided by the library.

Parameter.Name: title
Parameter.Abstract: String title of event

Parameter.Name: customDataSources
Parameter.Abstract: Dictionary of custom datasources (key/value pairs) to be included in the event dispatch. If a value is an array, be sure to use an array of strings.

Token.Abstract: Sends a view to Collect. Views are packaged with any custom key/value data sources passed in along with the default datasources provided by the library.

Parameter.Name: title
Parameter.Abstract: String title of view

Parameter.Name: customDataSources
Parameter.Abstract: Dictionary of custom datasources (key/value pairs) to be included in the event dispatch. If a value is an array, be sure to use an array of strings.

Token.Abstract: Sends an event to Collect. Events are packaged with any custom key/value data sources passed in along with the default datasources provided by the library.

Parameter.Name: Eventtype
Parameter.Abstract: enum: (TEALDispatchTypeActivity, TEALDispatchTypeConversion,TEALDispatchTypeDerived, TEALDispatchTypeInteraction, TEALDispatchTypeView)

Parameter.Name: CustomDataSources
Parameter.Abstract: Dictionary of custom datasources (key/value pairs) to be included in the event dispatch. If a value is an array, be sure to use an array of strings.

Parameter.Name: Title
Parameter.Abstract: String title of view

Parameter.Name: completion:
Parameter.Abstract: Optional completion handler returns dispatch status

Token.Abstract: Copy of all non persistent, UI object and dispatch specific data sources captured by a Tealium library instance at time of call.

ReturnValue.Abstract: NSDictionary of Tealium Data Source keys and values at time of call.

Token.Abstract: Adds additional data to the temporary data sources dictionary. This command is added to the end of the current Tealium background queue for writing.

Parameter.Name: additionalDataSources
Parameter.Abstract: New or overwrite data sources to add to the volatile data sources store. These key values can only be superceded by the custom data sources added to track calls. If a value is an array, be sure to use an array of strings.

Token.Abstract: Removes key-value pairs from the library instance's volatile memory

Parameter.Name: dataSourceKeys
Parameter.Abstract: An NSArray of string keys to remove

Token.Abstract: Copy of all long term Tealium data source data written to and read from disk, specific to a given library instance.

ReturnValue.Abstract: NSDictionary of Tealium Data Source keys and values at time of call.

Token.Abstract: Adds key-value info into the library instance's persistent data store. Use this to track lifetime values or seldom-changed global data sources.

Parameter.Name: additionalDataSources
Parameter.Abstract: An NSDictionary of string keys and values. If a value is an array, be sure to use an array of strings.

Token.Abstract: Removes all keys from array parameter.

Parameter.Name: dataSourceKeys
Parameter.Abstract: An NSArray of strings of the target keys to remove from the persistence store.

Token.Abstract: Joins an AudienceStream trace if either the Collect or TagManagement service are enabled.

Parameter.Name: token
Parameter.Abstract: String value should match the code provided via the AudienceStream web UI.

Token.Abstract: Stops sending trace data for the provided token in the joinTraceWithToken: method.

Parameter.Name: completion
Parameter.Abstract: An optional completion block.

Token.Abstract: The visitor profile url associated with the current user.
Where Collect will retrieve profile definitions.
Copy of the Unique visitor ID per Account / Device combination.

ReturnValue.Abstract: String value of the visitorID for the Account the library was enabled with.

Token.Abstract: Last retrieved profile instance. This is updated every time the profile is queried. Depending on the settings the library was enabled with, this could be after every sendEvent:customData: call or only on explicit request.

ReturnValue.Abstract: Returns valid TEALVisitorProfile object. Its properties might be nil of nothing is loaded into them yet.

Token.Abstract: Retrieves the current visitor profile from AudienceStream.

Parameter.Name: completion
Parameter.Abstract: Completion block with retrieved TEALVisitorProfile instance and an error should any problems occur.

Token.Abstract: Adds a remote command block that can be triggered by the instance's TIQ templates.

Parameter.Name: commandID
Parameter.Abstract: NSString that identifies this code block

Parameter.Name: description
Parameter.Abstract: Optional NSString description of the command block

Parameter.Name: queue
Parameter.Abstract: The dispatch queue to run the command on. Note, any UI commands must be done on the main thread.

Parameter.Name: responseBlock
Parameter.Abstract: An optional block that returns a TEALRemoteCommandResponse object whenever the command is executed.

Token.Abstract: Removes a remote command block for the given commandID

Parameter.Name: commandID
Parameter.Abstract: NSString identifier for the command block to remove.
